The Plateau for Atiku Movement, a group of PDP Elders, party chieftains and stakeholders from Plateau State who is committed to the victory of Alhaji Atiku Abubakar in the 2023 Presidential election have joined hosts of others to congratulate the Osun State Governor-elect, Senator Ademola Adeleke, over his victory at Saturday’s poll. Protem Secretary of the group, Professor Shedrach Best in a Press Statement issued in Jos on Monday and made available to Daily Independent in Jos, described the victory as well deserved and a victory for the Osun people and for democracy. Shadrach Best described “Senator Adeleke as a proud and worthy product of the PDP, a dogged fighter, a consistent democrat who has enjoyed the confidence of his people over the years” According to Professor Best,.eEven though victory had eluded Senator Adeleke under questionable circumstances in the past, the 16th July 2022 polls produced a convincing result that left nobody in doubt about the acceptance of Senator Adeleke by his people. Professor Best added, “We wish the Senator well as he prepares to govern Osun State, believing that he will give his citizens good governance and fulfil his campaign promises to the people of Osun State.” The group also commended the Presidential flag bearer of the PDP, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar, for providing the necessary leadership to warm up to the victory of the party in Osun State. ” It shows the readiness of the Party and the Candidate to coast to victory in the forthcoming General elections, and to provide good governance to the nation”. The Plateau Group congratulated the party leadership under the National Chairman, Senator Iyorchia Ayu, for putting the party back in winning ways, stressing that they are hopeful that Nigeria will taste democracy and good governance again under the new PDP President from May 29 2023″, the group stressed.